│  Architectural Patterns). Approximately 85% of analyzed open-source frameworks utilize such a modular architecture (Document: Core        │
│  Architectural Patterns).                                                                                                                 │
│  *   **Tool-Use Integration:** Critical for extending agent capabilities, this pattern enables agents to interact with external           │
│  environments, scientific instruments, APIs, and computational resources (e.g., Python interpreters, web search, specialized scientific   │
│  software) (Document: Core Architectural Patterns; MachineLearningMastery). This allows agents to perform actions beyond their core       │
│  reasoning engine. 78% of reviewed open-source frameworks integrate external tools or APIs (Document: Core Architectural Patterns). The   │
│  **ReAct Pattern** (Reasoning and Acting) is a specific manifestation of tool-use, combining reasoning (Chain-of-Thought) with            │
│  task-specific actions (LinkedIn; MachineLearningMastery).                                                                                │
